Title: Using std::array and using "array" as nameQuery: <p>In my C++ JSON library, I recently had a <a href="https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/590" rel="noreferrer">regression with GCC7</a>. I stripped down the affected code and hope to understand the error.</p>

<h1>The code</h1>

<p>Consider this header <code>myclass.hpp</code>:</p>

<pre><code>#pragma once

template &lt;typename X&gt;
struct A
{
    struct value_t
    {
        X array;
    };

    static A array()
    {
        return A();
    }

    friend bool operator&lt;(const A&amp; lhs, const A&amp; rhs) noexcept
    {
        return lhs.val.array &lt; rhs.val.array;
    }

    value_t val = {};  
};
</code></pre>

<p>As you see, I used the name "array" as member variable name in struct <code>value_t</code>, as name of a static function. I then included the header in the following file:</p>

<pre><code>#include &lt;array&gt;
using std::array; // note this!
#include "myclass.hpp"

int main()
{}
</code></pre>

